    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.20/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-11T10:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 11, 1940—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. In two separate conferences held today with the President and the Foreign
                        Minister<note n="21" xml:id="d104fn1">Alberto Echandi Montero.</note> I was
                    requested to cable the Department and urgently request the immediate despatch of
                    an American-Spanish speaking military mission to San José to prepare a plan upon
                    which the Costa Rican Government could base the reorganization of its military
                    establishment. Number of such commission not mentioned <pb facs="0101" n="89"
                        xml:id="pg_89"/> but Foreign Minister indicated that the study might require
                    some months. As a matter of policy most urgently recommend that this commission
                    be named at earliest possible date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
